<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900626-0113</DOCNO><DOCID>900626-0113.</DOCID><HL>   Meridian Insurance Sets Charge</HL><DATE>06/26/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C6</SO><CO>   MIGI</CO><LP>   INDIANAPOLIS -- Meridian Insurance Group Inc. said it willpost a second-quarter charge of about $2 million, citing theeffect of storms in early and mid-June. The insurer had ayear-earlier loss of $1.4 million.   The company said that despite a favorable trend in privatepassenger auto business, chances for a second-quarter profitare &quot;problematic,&quot; because of numerous claims from tornadodamage in parts of its marketing areas in Indiana, Ohio andIllinois.</LP><TEXT/></DOC>